quran[15]{c,v,t}:
  43,1,M. (Ha. Mim)
  43,2,By the clear (and clarifying) book
  43,3,Indeed We made it an Arabic Quran so that you may understand
  43,4,"And it is indeed in the main book with Us, (and it is) outstanding and wise"
  43,5,"Should We take the reminder away from you, ignoring you because you are excessive people"
  43,6,And how many prophets did We send among the earlier ones
  43,7,"And no prophet came to them, unless they were ridiculing him"
  43,8,"So We destroyed more courageous (and more powerful people) than them, and the example of the earlier ones passed by"
  43,9,"And if you ask them: who created the skies and the earth? They shall say: the powerful and the knowledgeable created them"
  43,10,The One who made the earth a bed for you and He made roadways for you in it so that you may be guided (and find your way)
  43,11,"And the One who sent down rain from the sky with (proper) measure, then We brought dead land back to life with it. That is how you are brought out"
  43,12,"And the One who created pairs of everything, and made the ships and the livestock for you to ride"
  43,13,"So that you settle on its back, then when you are settled on it remember the favor of your Master and say: glory to the One (who is flawless) who brought this under our control (to be of service to us) while we were not capable of it"
  43,14,And we certainly return to our Master
  43,15,And they made a part (an offspring) for Him from His servants. Indeed the human being is clearly ungrateful